The Ogun State Governor, Dapo Abiodun, on Monday urged the workers in the state to regularly check their health status to remain fit and productive for themselves and the state. Abiodun stated this at the inauguration of a health programme tagged, ‘Know Your Health Status,’ in commemoration of 2021 Public Service Day, at the Arcade ground, Oke-Mosan, Abeokuta. The governor, in a statement by the Press Officer, Office of the Head of Service, Passover Adeshina, urged the workers to pay attention to their health to diagnose any ailment early. He said, “Ogun State civil servants are the best one can get anywhere; do not allow any unscrupulous individual sabotage the existing standard and integrity of the civil service. I want to advise you to do a regular check-up to detect early, any ailment that may affect your work for the progress of the state.” He commended the workers for their productivity, noting that they had shown genuine commitment towards the realisation of the ‘Building Our Future Together’ agenda of his administration. The Head of Service, Alhaja Selimot Ottun, urged the workers to avail themselves of various medical tests available to know their health status and those given drugs to use them in accordance with the doctor’s prescription. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com